HEADWORD: Helipterum
<hw>Helipterum</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>genus of South African and
Australian herbs or shrubs grown as everlastings; the various
<gen>Helipterum</gen> species are currently in process of being assigned
to other genera, especially <gen>Pteropogon</gen> and
<gen>Hyalosperma</gen>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> genus <gen>Helipterum</gen>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

